{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dc0de193-819f-42f1-a659-569ca685b0d6","content":"Here's what you need for NativeAOT crash dump collection with `createdump`:\n\n**Pod spec changes:**\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n  - name: your-app\n    env:\n    # Enable crash dumps (1 = on)\n    - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n      value: \"1\"\n    # Dump type: 4 = full heap (MiniDumpWithFullMemory)\n    - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n      value: \"4\"\n    # Custom createdump path (NativeAOT has no runtime dir)\n    - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n      value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n    # Dump output path (%e=exe, %p=pid, %t=timestamp)\n    - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n      value: \"/tmp/coredumps/%e.%p.%t.dmp\"\n    # Optional: enable createdump diagnostic logging\n    - name: DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics\n      value: \"1\"\n    securityContext:\n      capabilities:\n        add:\n        # Required: createdump needs ptrace to attach to the crashing process\n        - SYS_PTRACE\n    volumeMounts:\n    - name: coredumps\n      mountPath: /tmp/coredumps\n  volumes:\n  - name: coredumps\n    emptyDir:\n      sizeLimit: 2Gi\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`SYS_PTRACE`** — required; `createdump` uses `ptrace` to read process memory.\n- **`DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath`** — essential for NativeAOT since there's no runtime directory for auto-discovery.\n- **`DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType`** — type `4` gives full memory; use `1` (normal) or `2` (with heap) for smaller dumps.\n- **`emptyDir` volume** — keeps dumps on the node. Swap for a PVC or sidecar exporter if you need persistence beyond pod lifetime.\n- **`sizeLimit`** — adjust based on your app's memory footprint; full dumps match RSS size.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b151ef85-b723-48b5-a63f-21c5e296fb32","outputTokens":556,"requestId":"4185:195805:6279660:6BB57BE:69F1633F"},"id":"21a06dc1-d250-4b85-9738-6318ee01b282","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:47:55.401Z","parentId":"1f86eaa9-d31f-4708-a441-7638bd8bd0f7"}
